details.description: Lottie’s Cafe is a cafe for the modern diner. Located in Uptown Charlotte, we are a coffee shop with extended food and tea offerings. All espresso and food is hand crafted. We feature a full espresso program, matcha, breakfast and lunch. We also offer Charlotte themed souvenirs and gifts.

reviews_data.review_text: I am giving perfect score for the customer service! Food was good but their friendliness and making each customer feel welcome is the highlight of our breakfast in this place. The person in the counter greets everyone with a genuine smile and very interactive with all the customers! Definitely will be coming back! We had really good experience.
Great coffee, food and service! Would definitely recommend to change up your work from home location.

I'm pretty particular when it comes to my espresso and this team knows what they're doing. They consistently create delicious drinks and they are incredibly friendly while they do it! Anytime I've been here the team has always been very warm and welcoming, with smiles on their faces and always a willingness to serve.

Working from home five days a week makes me appreciate a good coffee shop, and Lottie's was a fantastic find. I can't wait to go back.
I was really impressed with the food and drinks. The hash was delicious and flavorful, though I would have loved a little more of that creamy sauce. It paired perfectly with the lavender chai latte.The atmosphere is perfect for getting some work done. The space is bright and airy, with plenty of seating options for co-working. I also enjoyed the light music and the clean restrooms.

I visited Lottie’s yesterday (Sat morning) on a whim for a solo breakfast date. Lottie’s ended up feeding more than just my belly. It provided the calm I needed after a hectic week. I’ll just get the obvious out of the way… how delicious the food is. You can tell my Hugo’s Hash was handcrafted with love and the flavors all melted together. My plate didn’t stand a chance. As a huge coffee fan, I was pleasantly surprised how well balanced my Airplane Latte was, especially since I ordered it with light milk. It also, did not stand a chance. Even more notable than their amazing food, was the customer service I received. There was a light and just a positive spirit inside of the cafe. It also shined through the employees who not only care about your order, but care about you as a person.
My first experience at Lottie’s was truly a special one and I would recommend them a million times over. ❤️

This is my first time in Lottie's. The service is spot on. We dealt with Alicia, the manager. She was both very friendly and professional. This coffee shop makes you feel comfortable and the latte is spectacular. If you are in Charlotte, come to Lottie's.

My favorite coffee spot in Uptown, and it’s not very close!

The all day breakfast here is especially notable. Not your run of the mill offerings you get from other coffee shops where they microwave a bagel.

Recommend for breakfast or brunch highly!
Popped in for a coffee set. Lit
The Airplane Latte looks great, but it can get very messy when ordered to-go. The Biscoff on the outer layer ends up on your hands, car, and just about everywhere else.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Subaita. We have a description and photo of the airplane latte online. We are also always happy to make the latte iced without the decorated rim. We understand and respect it isn’t for everyone, you simply have to ask us to hold them rim. We would even have been happy to remake it if you had let us know it wasn’t your cup of tea. Please always afford us and any other eatery the opportunity to correct any dissatisfaction while you’re still with us.

reviews_data.review_text: Cute little café for a quick breakfast bite and to grab a coffee. Stopped here on the way to Museum of Illusions and Gantt Center, both a quick walk away.
Friendly staff, delicious food that's actually worth the money in my opinion, great coffee, and a cozy atmosphere. Will definitely come back if I'm in town!
Coffee and food were excellent. Lottie and her staff were exceptionally welcoming and kind. So glad we stopped in. Highly recommend ‼️
Soooo goodt!!
The best peach tea ever. Staff are super friendly. Overall very successful business, watch out Starbucks.

Great coffee and good food. Cosy chic interiors and a chilled vibe. Excellent service from Damian, what a top guy, best service we’ve had in a while - super friendly, extra helpful, polite and kind - thank you! Other staff should be inspired by Damian and take note!

Best Cafe in the city of Charlotte! Great service, great food, great drinks! The owner Ashley is a gift to the industry! She’s always present and interacting with her guests and her personality is amazing! Will support every chance I get!

Cafe owner from out of town and I visited here. I must say, I’m impressed. Very sweet staff and quick service. The place was clean and espresso was excellent, and I am quite picky! I look forward to coming back on my nest visit.

this place is a scam. the blonde front desk girl was so unfriendly and unpleasant. we were sitting eating our breakfast and a delivery man came in and dropped off a target bag of thomas bagels… simply lemonade and other prepackeged foods. it’s really upsetting to pay 7-14$ for breakfast and then watch them pour the lemonade into an unmarked container and charge premium pricing. Also serving thomas bagels that you can buy at the grocery store is boardline pathetic. Do better
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Marissa,
     I’m sorry to hear you were unsatisfied with your experience. We stand on good customer service and apologize you didn’t feel you received that. We receive our food from Gordon Food service once a week. When in a bind we have to choose between 1 star reviews of customers burdened with the common happening of an item being sold out or call for a quick Instacart to keep things in stock until our next Gordon shipment. While we personally find microwaving Jimmy Dean sandwiches and passing them off as scratch made to be the real scam, we  have chosen to assemble sandwiches ourselves instead. We do not scam, we are who we say we ware. We specialize in craft coffee, matcha and small breakfast bites. We source our pastries from local bakers as we are not bakers and our kitchen doesn’t have the capacity to develop a wide variety of pastries. Our prices are in line with every mid size coffee shop we know if not lower for uptown. We appreciate the feedback and hope you have a great summer.

reviews_data.review_text: Warm and inviting staff serve up delicious beverages and food in a fresh and clean shop!  Can't decide what to order?  Ask your server about some of their custom creations!   It's my go-to spot every afternoon!

If you’re seeking incredible coffee and food that is authentically Charlotte, while supporting a family owned small business, in a chic yet welcoming space then Lottie’s is a must try! The iced airplane latte was delicious and full of flavor without being too sweet; a thoughtfully crafted, balanced masterpiece. The Hugo’s hash was hearty and tasty without leaving you feeling heavy or sluggish. Best of all was the friendly, hospitable, smiling service and ownership! I can’t wait for my next visit to Lottie’s Cafe. Highly recommend!
Went here for breakfast. Their avocado toast is fantastic. Great ambience, central location, and friendly staff.

Lottie’s such an amazing place. The staff always treats me like family. Whether it’s coffee, lemonade, or a pastry everything is delicious. If you want a great friendly place come relax, come check them out.

I just love this adorable place! My friend and I stumbled upon this gem of a cafe walking uptown and couldn't be more pleased. The food was fantastic, coffee was tasty and the staff was so sweet and accommodating. Definitely recommend and will be back!

Me and my sister came here today, today was my first time but she comes often for work. I loved the vibes of this place it’s so welcoming. I had a Hugo’s hash and a coconut cream latte which was bomb. Will be back

Lottie’s has been my safe space for work, I absolutely enjoy the environment.
Food is amazing and I love the iced lattes. Staff has always been very good to me. No regrets! ❤️

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: This was our first time going to Lottie’s and the atmosphere and vibe were amazing. The service was a weird experience. We made it known this was our first time. I asked for clarification on a drink I wanted to order but got very dry and non helpful responses. The overall energy of the person taking our order made both my friend and I a little uncomfortable. It was not a welcoming experience. We still proceeded to place the order anyway. When we received our drinks and food, my drink was not at all what the staff member taking our order explained. I received a cup of ice with an expresso shot in it, not even a full drink. When I attempted to get understanding from another staff member we received the same passive dry energy. The food was delicious. It was just a disappointment to have experienced the service we did.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Najha, I hate that this was your perception. I’m the owner and I watched the interaction between you all. While the confusion regarding the drink order was clear, it seemed to be worked out pleasantly. I have a tendency to jump in but thought I’d let staff work it out. I observed her smile multiple times and she corrected the drink. Friendly service is our goal and we hate you feel we missed the mark. We appreciate the compliments about the food and we hope you return for a better experience.

reviews_data.review_text: This is a very cute spot for coffee to go or coffee to stay and relax. Tried the Airplane ice latte and I highly recommend. Just the right amount of sweetness for a yummy coffee. If you haven’t been- just go and try! You won’t be disappointed.

Enjoyed my visit to this beautiful uptown coffee shop today. The avocado toast and iced matcha with strawberry puree were delicious and the customer service was excellent! If you want food made for you and not zapped in a microwave, this is your place.
Delicious oat milk iced lattes in a hot day and  breakfast, quick service.
This coffee shop is a beautiful space. The staff is sweet and the coffee is good.

I visited this coffee shop today after seeing so many great reviews and social media buzz, and I had pretty high expectations. I ordered a strawberry matcha latte, hoping for a strawberry puree, but instead, it was made with strawberry syrup, and the almond milk overpowered the matcha flavor. It just wasn’t the combination I was hoping for.

I also tried the Hugo’s hash brown bowl. Unfortunately, there was a mix-up with my egg preference. I prefer my eggs fried over hard, and even though I went back to let them know, I still ended up with a runny egg, which I couldn’t enjoy.

The overall service felt a bit off, too. The staff member who helped me seemed low-energy and not very enthusiastic about guiding a new customer. It was a bit uncomfortable not getting any recommendations or much interaction.

Overall, I was hoping for a better experience, especially given the hype. Hopefully, it was just an off day!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Yiny,
    We truly pride ourselves on selves on proving excellent customer service. We apologize if your expectations were not met. Everyone has off days but you can’t redo a customers first experience. I’ll provide this feedback to the team and I hope you give us another try on the house.

reviews_data.review_text: small,  quaint,  friendly,  quick.   enjoyed the food.
Nice Place.
Amazing service, extremely friendly and inviting. Highly recommend if in the Charlotte area.
Really cute coffee shop in downtown Charlotte. Great branding, great vibes, and good coffee!
The nicest people and the best coffee!
Great coffee and super quick service!
Ok and nice view
Get the airplane latte that’s all I have to say!!

Not impressed. Avocado toast w egg and bacon is very bland. Tried to order the bagel sandwich and they are out of everything bagels. It's a Sunday morning come on. Very overpriced for what you get. Won't be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Jim,
     I’m sorry today’s visit didn’t live up
To your expectations. Please note that we are subject to suppliers being sold out of things like every other eatery in town. Our supplier delivered 2 out of 10 cases of ordered bagels so we get your frustration. While we feel our prices are in line with other like cafes, we respect your opinion. Have the best of Sundays.

reviews_data.review_text: Good coffee and great place to get some work done. I didn’t get any food, but anything coming out for brunch looked amazing too.

Can't comment on the food because I didn't purchase any but the iced coffee and cappuccino that I ordered were good. Very cute shop with plenty of seating  (indoor and outdoor) for gathering or working independently. Also has a gift shop area to purchase goods.
I had the pleasure of meeting the owner and she was so kind! The food was amazing and I loved the little store, I even purchased a t-shirt. 10/10 recommend stopping by!
good and cozy place to hang around and work. great iced latte.
Their hours claim to open at 7am (even on their website). I walked 10 minutes to get here and waited until 7:15am and still closed.
Yes, you have to get the airplane latte 🩷 I also had the avocado toast and it was excellent!

Chef's Kiss!! This place is Ah-mazing and will be my go-to spot for sure when I'm Uptown! Food is delicious and my café drink was so yummy! The staff was helpful and friendly. The place is super clean and architecturally pleasing! Lastly, the choice of music is good playing while you dine is great. 10 out of 10! Job well done!
Gorgeous coffee shop. Perfect to work, sit & read, or enjoy coffee with a friend. Also merch was adorable and so soft! Clear intention was put into the establishment.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Kayla! So nice to meet you today! We are so glad you felt the intention inside our space. Hope to visit with you again! Enjoy your coffee sweatshirt!

reviews_data.review_text: Impeccable vibes

Short: You need to make this one your coffee shop!

Long: I wanted to meet some of my clients here for coffee. I got there around 940. The space felt so fresh and homey. I ordered the apple fritter warmed, and it hit the spot. I later found out they have some meals as well. When my client got there, they ordered the iced coffee and did 2 more pastries. They said the biscoff donut was a 10, as someone who makes their own desserts. The shop later turned into a networking experience with a dj and bingo cards to connect with others in the room. I was happy to have picked this day to come and would definitely come back.
Amazing coffee and atmosphere! Came from out of state with a coworker and we both said we wished we could bottle this place and take it home!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Where did you come from? Maybe we can come!! Thanks for coming!

reviews_data.review_text: Great location and coffee!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Andy! Come see us when you’re nearby!

reviews_data.review_text: The cappuccino was delicious and a super cute place to work at.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Paola! We appreciate the feedback and look forward to your next visit!

reviews_data.review_text: such a cute cafe! the airplane latte was delicious and not too sweet. the staff are very friendly. the location itself is very bright and aesthetically pleasing.
Very cozy cafe. High quality coffee! 👍
The food and coffee there are really delicious! Tried Deluxe Avocado Toast and French fries (which are more like potato bites) with a side of bacon and a cappuccino.

Great little café with good atmosphere and free wi-fi. Ended up with a free barista-made coffee due to the last day of a promo event. Due to the promo event, the food did take a little longer but they checked with me when ordering if that was okay.

Unfortunately it seems that someone else took a small part of my food order (on a seperate plate), but the staff were doing the best they could and they had my back 👍

This place is the BESt coffee shop in Charlotte! The staff are so nice and attentive. It's a great place to come and work while
Enjoying some yummy food and an even better latte! 10 out of 10!!!

Amazing location!! Today was my first day visiting after hearing wonderful things. It was so busy today! Some event with Home Depot providing free coffee and a donut had the place jam packed. The staff was very delightful and had a decent pace under such a heavy workload from traffic. Food was great, I recommend a hash bowl! My latte was cool and tasty. Someone came to my table to check on me and collect my plate (that I licked clean😬), I’ll be back for sure!!!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Hugo’S Hash, Donut, Avocado Toast, Iced Latte

reviews_data.review_text: My experience is always great when I come to Lotties! Ashley brought me my items and made sure I had everything I needed, I will 100% be back!

Lottie’s was such an amazing experience. From the moment you walk in to the time you leave you feel the welcoming energy. Ashley was amazing. She bought my food and drinks right to my table. Definitely will be coming back.

The most wonderful experience at Lottie’s Cafe! We went when it was very busy which I took as a good sign. The staff was amazing, the food was hot and delicious, and the coffee was made with love!❤️ and you can tell the staff was experienced!!

Kudos to the kitchen for making such delicious food during such a rush! Can’t wait to come back!!

I love spending time at Lottie’s! The aesthetic is everything and staff is so accommodating. I’ll stop by for a change of scenery while working or a weekend pick me up! My favorites are the matcha and Hugo Hash.

Heard great things about this place but unfortunately my visit was not great at all. Waited for about 45 minutes for 3 bagel sandwiches. Once the bagels were finally given to us one was wrong. They went back to change it, as I am watching them the cook touched my bagel with his bare hands. Which is very disgusting. Water spilled on the table and floor we told them and they said there are napkins over there. What kind of service is that? Not happy with this visit at all!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi K’Janei,
     Owner here who was on shift during your visit. I’m so sorry that your visit didn’t meet your expectations. The things you’ve heard are consistent experiences that we strive to give every visit. While we may not always nail it, especially on event days like today, we always want to leave customers satisfied. Our dedication to community engagement events called for a visibly larger crowd due to FREE coffee and pastries being offered. We appreciate feedback especially in person when possible. We are ALWAYS happy to give refunds and redos. Cleanliness and following food safety is a priority and we will be review what you’ve shared. Again, we would’ve gladly received the feedback in person and appreciated the chance to make amends. A staff member did direct you to napkins when requested. Once you stated there was a spill, she left to grab proper tools to clean the spill.  We do not carry a protocol of leaving a customer to clean a spill independently. While we hope you come back on another day for a different experience, we appreciate the feedback and will work to improve productivity on busy days.

reviews_data.review_text: Really great spot, would for sure recommend stopping in! We had the iced coffee, the airplane donut & blueberry muffin, and all were spot on. The staff were super friendly & the shop was so cute to be in. Wish we would have tried more!
I stopped by to have a coffee and enjoyed the space. I’ll certainly be frequenting here more often.

Black Owned. Located at the Epi Center. Good food and drinks. Great hang out spot. I spent $15 on my pork, egg, and cheese bagel sandwich and a biscotti iced coffee ( you can't beat it). Indoor and outdoor seating. Parking decks are nearby, but I came on a Sunday and metered parking was cheaper/free.

This place is so cute and clean. My husband and I decided to go for our weekly family meeting and loved it. We both and the Airplane Latte, mine iced and his hot, delicious. The food was an outstanding too. We will be back for sure.

Fantastic atmosphere! Friendly staff, great seating amd the recommended Hot Airplane Latte that was suggested to me was very good.
Highly recommend this cafe!
Bagels were good but coffee wasn’t up to the mark
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Surabhi! We always want you to have the experience you hoped for and appreciate the feedback while you’re right there with us :) We will always correct, remake or refund while you’re inside of our space. We hope you visit again for a re-do.

reviews_data.review_text: Lottie’s was a lovely find for us while traveling in Charlotte. The food and drinks were absolutely delicious, the vibe was bright, clean, and relaxed, and the staff could not have been nicer. Definitely stop here if you have the chance!

First time trying today and was AMAZING!!! Friendly and welcoming Woman on the register, even spelled my name right! 🤣 because they are so many different spellings of my name. Ordered a Chai Tea Latte and caramel 🍩 which was thee BEST 🍩 that I've ever had!!! Well worth the money!!!! Beautiful decorations and was quite busy. Highly recommend and will be back! Thank you for making my morning!

This naturally sun lit coffee shop was very pleasant. I love that they serve breakfast all day and have plenty of seating. I was able to vibe out and get a lot of work done. And did I mention it is Black-Owned in the heart of the city!

review_questions.Parking options: Paid parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.review_text: This might have been the best donut I’ve ever had. Such a great spot to relax with a good cup of coffee.
This cafe was so inviting. From the atmosphere to the service, you will feel so welcome and comfortable. Will definitely visit again while in NC.

This place is highly underrated. There are no words that will do it justice. From the perfectly presented and delicious bagel to the excellent customer service, this is truly a great place. Indulge yourself in the delicious airplane latte made to perfection and topped off with a biscoff. I also had the pleasure to try the airplane donut, but it was so good that I forgot to take a picture of it. If you're craving a great breakfast, this is the place to go!
reviews_data.owner_answer: There is nothing like seeing a review like this first thing in the morning! I’ll be sure to share your feedback with the team! Thank you so much for visiting!

reviews_data.review_text:
Amazing coffee, engaging staff and ... rosemary honey donuts.
Whoops, who ate that? 🤯
reviews_data.owner_answer: Andrew… I do wonder who are that 😏 thank you so much for sharing your review! I will brag on our staff today! Please come back and see us.

reviews_data.review_text: Great spot for coffee and food! The deluxe avo is delicious and the lattes and americanos were well made.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Meredith, thank you so much for visiting and leaving a review for Lottie’s! We are thrilled you enjoyed your experience. We look forward to seeing you again!

reviews_data.review_text:
I visited this café and had eggs, turkey sausage patties, and a matcha, and everything was absolutely delicious! They were also incredibly accommodating when it came to my food allergies, which made the experience even better. The staff was friendly and attentive, and I really appreciated how thoughtful they were. I can’t wait to come back again soon!

P.S. The brisket French toast was my nieces and she said it was delicious also.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Amanda, we are proud to hear you were well taken care of during your visit. We will be sure to share your thoughts with this team. This helps to keep our team consistent and on track! We hope you visit again, soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Went by for breakfast on a road trip with my friends. Food/coffee was excellent, and the staff was super friendly. Fantastic way to start the day.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Hayes, we love a good road trip too! We are so glad you included Lottie’s in your journey. Should you ever journey this way again, please stop by and say hi!

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee was good.  I got their seasonal wonderland. It was not a cup of sugar.  I could taste the spices.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Teresa,
   There is no greater compliment than knowing you could taste the components of our well thought out drinks. We will be smiling from your review! Come see us again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I came to this unassuming coffee shop back when it was only a few months old. And almost ever single day, I have made it a priority to spend my morning here. Absolutely wonderful coffee and food, and the servers are a delight to get to know. Happy to be a regular here and happy to have found this place. Highly recommend.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We have so enjoyed getting to know you and coming to expect your visit. You’ve been encouraging and a bright spot in the start of our story. Cheers to many more coffees and chats with you!

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing coffee, staff was very nice. Cozy vibe and great food. 10/10 would go again.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We will take that 10, Wesley! Thank you so much for coming and enjoying Lottie’s. We hope you visit again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: LOTTIES CAFE. Is so amazing, the workers are so nice. The food is to die for. I visited NC Charlotte two weeks ago and I went back to Lottie’s twice in my weekend trip. Most definitely will be going back soon
reviews_data.owner_answer: Corrine, thank you so much. We are honored you choice to visit more than once. This means so much to our team. We hope to see you on your next trip!

reviews_data.review_text:
I love coming to Lottie’s Cafe.  The atmosphere is always welcoming and the teas are delicious!  I also enjoyed the pastries! It is a gorgeous space!

Thank you for the outstanding service!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Shawna,
     There is nothing we love more than a repeat customer. Thank you for your ongoing support and making us a stop when you’re in town!

reviews_data.review_text: Wonderful and cute coffee shop. Lattes were delicious!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Mark! We look forward to hearing of the adventures of your family soon. Stay in touch!

reviews_data.review_text: We were in town visiting family and happened into Lottie's. Aside from the great coffee drinks and food, the staff is phenomenal! And a special shout out to Teagan, who was our barista.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We adore Teagan and we are glad that you do too! Thanks for visiting us and we hope to see you soon.

reviews_data.review_text: I dined at Lottie's on Sunday with my grandchildren. They were so attentive to the little ones and my decaf latte was perfect. I tried the Savory French Toast and I am a big fan. Though I do not live close, I hope to get back to Lottie's again soon. Charlotte, you have a true gem in the middle of Uptown.
reviews_data.owner_answer: You are so kind! We are glad you rebooted your visit with your grandchildren. We hope to see you again very soon.

reviews_data.review_text: I pass this place every day and figured I would give it a try. That proved to be one of the worst mistakes I’ve made in awhile. I ordered a quadruple espresso, and I watched the employee only make 2 shots, so they essentially ripped me off, but that’s beside the point. This drink was vile! Hands down, the worst espresso/coffee I’ve ever had in my life— actually, I think it was the worst drink I’ve ever had in my life. Period. I don’t know if they were trying to play a prank, or simply forgot the clean the machine. But, it tasted like they put about half a cup of salt into the coffee, or possibly some cleaning solution. This was awful, and I regret even trying this place. Please do yourself, and your taste buds, a favor and avoid this place at all costs!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Mike,
    Owner here. As a serious espresso drinker, I hear and receive your concerns. I would love to chat about when your visit took place so that I can track down the order and who/how it was made. We value nothing more than getting it right and would love a chance to give you a better experience and the drink you actually ordered. As a small family owned business, we would appreciate direct feedback as we can’t always be on site watching over our establishment. Trust that we care about the results and want to hear your constructive thoughts. 

I also want to add that like every workplace, new employees are hired and take time to train. As you can see by the other reviews of other serious coffee drinkers, their experience was not yours. We are always more than willing to re do or refund if you’re not pleased.

reviews_data.review_text: I had such a great time at the bagel shop! Damien, the super energetic and friendly guy behind the counter, made the whole experience even better. His enthusiasm was infectious, and he made ordering a breeze. The Christmas decorations were absolutely charming, adding a cozy, festive vibe to the whole place. It’s the perfect spot to relax, hang out, or even knock out some homework. Definitely a 10/10 I highly recommend!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Damien is a gem and we are so happy he is a part of the team! Thanks for visiting Lottie’s and sharing your experience!

reviews_data.review_text: Lottie’s has quickly become one of my favorite places to be. The ladies and a few gentlemen behind the counter are friendly and attentive. It honestly feels like a little hometown shop in the middle of the city. I will be back!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Alicia,
     Hometown feeling is the goal! We are so glad you feel it!

reviews_data.review_text: Nice place but the service is awful.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Wow Adelina, owner here. I was actually on shift during your visit. You seemed to get your drinks pretty quickly and the interaction was brief and courteous. I’m sorry to hear that the service was not up to your standards today. We take customer service very seriously as you can see by the other reviews. Friendliness to each other and our patrons is top priority. If you’d like to share more details about why you feel this way, we would love to hear. Nostalgiahollow@gmail.com

reviews_data.review_text: It has such a cozy atmosphere and its spacious. The airplane latte was incredible.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Mirela, we appreciate your support and sharing your experience! Please come back and see us again.

reviews_data.review_text: Legit the best coffee shop ive been to in a long time. There is of course many good ones in clt but this one surpasses them by far. Its a cozy vibe as soon as you enter! But the breakfast sandwich I had …… CMON it was totally made with love and you can’t get that just anywhere. The snickerdoodle latte I had with oatmilk was so smooth I felt like I was drinking a cinnamon cloud but like with espresso and oatmilk ofc. The staff is so nice too I just wanted to give everyone a hug for providing such a nice cafe. I love lottie’s and after this experience, I feel like lottie’s loves me too ☺️💓

I’m so glad Lottie’s opened in Charlotte. We needed this.

They are a great addition to Uptown and the rebranded EpiCenter which is now known as The Queen City Quarter. As one of their anchor tenants, they’re in a prime and accessible location. You can dine inside or at one of the few tables on the patio.

The food here is delicious. It’s prepared by a local chef, Maria Martinez, who is a young phenomenon. The owner Ashley is amazing and the two of them work together to bring some of the most balanced, nutritious, and comforting dishes to life.

Service here is also exceptional. One of my favorite things to do when in I’m here is to chat with staff. They are pleasant it feels like you’ve stopped in your neighborhood corner cafe.

It honestly gives my Lowcountry vibes with the linen, open and bright vibes.

Sometimes, there are out of my favorite things, but I don’t hold it against them. They’re busy and that’s a good thing. I love to see small businesses flourishing and I hope to support them during their tenure Uptown — and maybe you will too!

Fave items: Hugo’s Hash, Beattie’s Bagel, George’s Sammie, the BBQ Chicken Flatbread, and the Shrimp & Grits when they have them! Don’t sleep on the Airplane Latte or their chai tea latte options. Always great!

Wow, Asha!!! We can’t appreciate your review or your frequent visits enough. We love to see you coming and look forward to your next visits. 

Sharing is such a vital part of the survivability of small businesses. We appreciate all you do for us and all small businesses in the area!
